id: pmc-xl7x
title: Make body enrichment registry resolution best-effort
description: Gemini review on pm-cli PR #113 found that pm-changelog body enrichment swallows readSettings failures but can still throw if item type registry resolution or settings-derived fields are malformed. Keep changelog generation best-effort by guarding the entire setup block upstream in pm-changelog rather than patching the managed extension copy in pm-cli.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags: []
created_at: "2026-06-05T16:38:07.198Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-05T16:39:41.552Z"
author: codex-pm-changelog-followup
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-05T16:39:16.904Z",codex-pm-changelog-followup,"Evidence: guarded readSettings, resolveItemTypeRegistry, id_prefix, and item_format setup in enrichItemBodies so --body-preview leaves front matter unchanged if registry/settings resolution fails. Verification passed locally: npm test (build + build:test + node --test dist-test/*.js, 85 tests). Linked sandbox-safe equivalent: PM_PATH=/tmp/pm-changelog-test-pm PM_GLOBAL_PATH=/tmp/pm-changelog-test-global npm test."
files[3]{path,scope,note}:
  dist/extension.js,project,Built package artifact for extension runtime
  dist/extension.js.map,project,Built source map for extension runtime
  src/extension.ts,project,Guard body enrichment setup as best-effort
